1
00:00:10,233 --> 00:00:12,100
<i>What are you and Hazel
doing here?</i>

2
00:00:12,233 --> 00:00:15,767
<i>How did you even find Manuel
and Felma? Huh?</i>

3
00:00:15,900 --> 00:00:16,600
<i> Yes! How?</i>

4
00:00:16,733 --> 00:00:18,933
<i>- Because of you!
- Huh?</i>

5
00:00:19,067 --> 00:00:21,633
<i> When you video-called Hazel.</i>

6
00:00:21,767 --> 00:00:24,200
<i>Fine, you're the one
Manuel loves.</i>

7
00:00:24,333 --> 00:00:28,767
<i>But I am still the one
and only Mrs. Cruz.</i>

8
00:00:28,900 --> 00:00:32,567
<i>Your name may be
on the paper as his wife,</i>

9
00:00:32,700 --> 00:00:37,733
<i>but my name is carved
in Manuel's heart.</i>

10
00:00:37,900 --> 00:00:44,433
<i>And you can never
erase that, Hazel.</i>

11
00:00:44,567 --> 00:00:46,300
<i>Take care of them for me, okay?</i>

12
00:00:46,433 --> 00:00:48,767
<i> And take care of yourself.</i>

13
00:00:48,900 --> 00:00:50,033
<i> I will.</i>

14
00:01:21,200 --> 00:01:22,000
Manuel.

15
00:01:23,033 --> 00:01:24,467
Manuel.

16
00:01:34,633 --> 00:01:35,867
Are you ready?

17
00:01:39,767 --> 00:01:41,033
No.

18
00:01:45,733 --> 00:01:46,967
But it has to be done.

19
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:04,267
Let's go.

20
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:11,433
Dad?

21
00:02:12,833 --> 00:02:15,067
Dad? Dad?

22
00:02:15,233 --> 00:02:16,567
- Jeff.
- Mom?

23
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:19,267
Ah...

24
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:20,467
- Where are you going?
- Son...

25
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:23,267
Son, lower your voice.

26
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:25,167
You might wake your siblings up.

27
00:02:26,267 --> 00:02:27,500
No, where are you going?

28
00:02:28,867 --> 00:02:30,267
Wait, I'm getting nervous,
I have a bad feeling.

29
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,700
I'm really nervous.

30
00:02:31,833 --> 00:02:32,733
Where are you going?

31
00:02:32,867 --> 00:02:34,133
Because, son, your...

32
00:02:36,100 --> 00:02:37,300
Because your...

33
00:02:37,433 --> 00:02:39,333
- What?
- Your father...

34
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:43,800
Felma, come on.

35
00:02:43,933 --> 00:02:45,367
Let's tell Jeff.

36
00:02:51,333 --> 00:02:54,300
Son, I'm going back to Hazel.

37
00:02:59,733 --> 00:03:00,800
What?

38
00:03:02,500 --> 00:03:04,433
Jeff, we'll explain.

39
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:07,500
We'll explain everything, dear.

40
00:03:16,333 --> 00:03:18,133
Oh, see?

41
00:03:18,267 --> 00:03:19,467
All set.

42
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:22,633
Wow.

43
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:28,867
Friend, you're so extra
with that welcome.

44
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,500
You cleaned all day?

45
00:03:31,633 --> 00:03:34,433
Oh... don't expect too much.

46
00:03:34,567 --> 00:03:36,033
What did you say?

47
00:03:36,167 --> 00:03:37,400
<i> Calling Dr. Fulgencio.</i>

48
00:03:37,533 --> 00:03:39,633
<i> Dr. Fulgencio, please proceed</i>

49
00:03:39,767 --> 00:03:41,600
<i>to the emergency room
nurse's station.</i>

50
00:03:42,733 --> 00:03:44,700
I'm just a concerned friend.

51
00:03:44,833 --> 00:03:46,567
You might end up disappointed.

52
00:03:48,033 --> 00:03:51,467
You saw how happy
they were at the resort, right?

53
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:54,700
What if he changed his mind
and doesn't show up?

54
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:57,767
<i>Alice, please,
don't annoy me.</i>

55
00:03:58,900 --> 00:04:00,833
Manuel will come.

56
00:04:00,967 --> 00:04:01,767
Because if he doesn't...

57
00:04:03,267 --> 00:04:05,033
he'll regret it.

58
00:04:05,167 --> 00:04:06,833
Coleen will rot in jail.

59
00:04:09,367 --> 00:04:10,400
Bye.

60
00:04:25,133 --> 00:04:26,333
So that's why we went
on that trip?

61
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:28,833
Because that's where
you'll say goodbye?

62
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:33,567
That's why you were saying all
that stuff to Andrea and me?

63
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:38,167
Because you're leaving us?

64
00:04:41,667 --> 00:04:42,633
No!

65
00:04:43,733 --> 00:04:44,733
No one's leaving this house!

66
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:46,700
You're not going back
to that woman!

67
00:04:48,733 --> 00:04:50,367
Dad, you're not going back
to her!

68
00:04:53,700 --> 00:04:55,533
Calm down.

69
00:04:55,667 --> 00:04:56,767
Calm down, son.

70
00:04:57,800 --> 00:05:00,033
This isn't just
your father's decision.

71
00:05:00,167 --> 00:05:02,300
- It's our decision.
- Mom, why did you agree?

72
00:05:05,467 --> 00:05:06,733
Dad, how could you let
this happen?

73
00:05:07,867 --> 00:05:10,833
You'll leave Mom, me,
Coleen, and Andrea

74
00:05:10,967 --> 00:05:13,467
for that evil woman?

75
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:14,667
You're going back to her?

76
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:20,400
Jeffrey.

77
00:05:20,533 --> 00:05:22,667
Jeffrey, calm down.

78
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:25,567
This isn't just
your father's decision.

79
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:27,467
It's our decision.

80
00:05:28,967 --> 00:05:32,133
What? Why?

81
00:05:32,267 --> 00:05:33,300
For what?

82
00:05:35,833 --> 00:05:37,367
For Coleen.

83
00:05:43,867 --> 00:05:45,600
So this is it.

84
00:05:45,733 --> 00:05:49,100
The thing you said
could help Coleen's case?

85
00:05:49,233 --> 00:05:51,300
To accept Hazel's offer?

86
00:05:52,900 --> 00:05:54,367
Son, it's the only way.

87
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:56,367
Dad, no.

88
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:57,500
You're not going back there.

89
00:05:57,633 --> 00:05:58,933
You're not leaving this house.

90
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:01,267
You're not leaving us.

91
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:03,600
You're not going back
to that evil woman.

92
00:06:03,733 --> 00:06:05,200
Because you're supposed
to stay here with us!

93
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:10,033
Our decision won't change.

94
00:06:17,700 --> 00:06:19,300
- Andrea!
- Jeff!

95
00:06:19,433 --> 00:06:21,067
Andrea! Coleen!

96
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:22,233
- Andrea! Coleen!
- Jeff, wait!

97
00:06:22,367 --> 00:06:24,100
- Jeff, no!
- Wait!

98
00:06:30,433 --> 00:06:31,300
Andrea!

99
00:06:31,433 --> 00:06:33,567
Sweetheart, no, no! Don't!

100
00:06:33,700 --> 00:06:36,567
Don't tell your siblings.

101
00:06:36,700 --> 00:06:38,933
Mom, they need to know.

102
00:06:39,067 --> 00:06:40,567
You're both so selfish!

103
00:06:43,833 --> 00:06:44,900
Okay fine!

104
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,533
Fine, I won't go,
I'll stay here.

105
00:06:48,667 --> 00:06:50,100
I won't go back to Hazel.

106
00:06:52,233 --> 00:06:53,733
But we must prepare ourselves

107
00:06:53,867 --> 00:06:55,167
for the possibility that Coleen
will end up in jail.

108
00:06:56,333 --> 00:06:58,200
And we won't have her
with us anymore.

109
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:03,567
I don't want to go back
to Hazel either.

110
00:07:05,967 --> 00:07:07,767
Just thinking about living

111
00:07:07,900 --> 00:07:10,100
in the same house
without Jessica...

112
00:07:11,833 --> 00:07:13,200
already makes me sick.

113
00:07:15,867 --> 00:07:18,033
But I have to swallow that...

114
00:07:19,067 --> 00:07:21,433
so Coleen's future
won't be ruined.

115
00:07:23,033 --> 00:07:24,533
Dad, we're whole now.

116
00:07:27,033 --> 00:07:30,000
Me, Mom, you, Andrea,
and Coleen.

117
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,600
You know, after that outing...

118
00:07:36,233 --> 00:07:38,067
after all the chaos...

119
00:07:39,367 --> 00:07:41,300
I thought that's
what we'd be every day.

120
00:07:43,033 --> 00:07:44,833
Complete...

121
00:07:46,267 --> 00:07:49,467
together... happy.

122
00:07:49,633 --> 00:07:50,967
Son, I'm sorry.

123
00:07:53,467 --> 00:07:56,700
I'm sorry I have to leave
and hurt you all again.

124
00:07:57,700 --> 00:07:59,000
Sorry.

125
00:08:00,567 --> 00:08:01,833
Son.

126
00:08:02,533 --> 00:08:04,567
Son, listen.

127
00:08:05,867 --> 00:08:10,533
Son, this is a huge sacrifice
for your father.

128
00:08:12,167 --> 00:08:13,900
A huge sacrifice.

129
00:08:15,033 --> 00:08:17,567
Remember that I love you all, so
much.

130
00:08:21,067 --> 00:08:23,667
This hurts me deeply.

131
00:08:26,567 --> 00:08:29,600
You know the kind of pain
that never goes away?

132
00:08:29,733 --> 00:08:33,233
Like being stabbed
and the knife never taken out.

133
00:08:33,367 --> 00:08:35,733
Every day,
the wound stays fresh.

134
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:40,133
Son, please,
I'm begging you.

135
00:08:42,267 --> 00:08:44,633
Don't tell your siblings.

136
00:08:47,900 --> 00:08:53,300
I'll just let them hate me
if they want.

137
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:56,200
It's better than Coleen
going to jail.

138
00:08:59,933 --> 00:09:01,633
Because if she goes to jail,

139
00:09:01,767 --> 00:09:04,033
we'll all be imprisoned
in sadness.

140
00:09:12,533 --> 00:09:13,900
Dad, is there really no...

141
00:09:16,233 --> 00:09:18,200
Dad, is there really no other
way?

142
00:09:19,667 --> 00:09:22,367
No other way to save Coleen?

143
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:24,467
None, son.

144
00:09:25,967 --> 00:09:27,467
This is the only one.

145
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:43,367
You're leaving us again!

146
00:09:47,733 --> 00:09:49,767
Son... Jeffrey.

147
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:54,300
Jeffrey, take your father.

148
00:09:55,933 --> 00:09:59,033
I don't want to see
Hazel ever again.

149
00:10:16,900 --> 00:10:18,500
When will we see you again?

150
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,800
I don't know, son.

151
00:10:26,100 --> 00:10:29,333
But maybe it's better
if you don't for now.

152
00:10:34,633 --> 00:10:35,867
Jeff, son...

153
00:10:39,467 --> 00:10:42,300
Take care of your siblings,
okay?

154
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:44,333
And your mom.

155
00:10:44,467 --> 00:10:45,967
You've done it before.

156
00:10:48,100 --> 00:10:50,467
You'll be the man
of the house for now.

157
00:10:52,633 --> 00:10:54,333
Take care of them.

158
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:56,700
<i> Jeffrey, you'll be</i>

159
00:10:56,833 --> 00:10:58,733
<i>the man of the house now, okay?</i>

160
00:10:58,867 --> 00:11:01,233
<i>You'll be
your mother's partner...</i>

161
00:11:01,367 --> 00:11:03,467
<i> and your siblings' support.</i>

162
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:06,067
<i>Take good care of them,
do you understand?</i>

163
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:07,367
<i> Yes, Dad.</i>

164
00:11:08,733 --> 00:11:11,933
This is exactly
how we said goodbye before.

165
00:11:14,633 --> 00:11:15,967
It just hurts more now.

166
00:11:18,633 --> 00:11:20,733
Back then, I took you
to the airport.

167
00:11:23,767 --> 00:11:26,300
I didn't know another woman
would take you from us.

168
00:11:28,333 --> 00:11:31,900
Now I'm taking you back
to that same woman,

169
00:11:32,933 --> 00:11:34,967
who I know will take you again.

170
00:11:42,933 --> 00:11:44,800
Dad, I'm going
to miss you again.

171
00:11:56,133 --> 00:11:57,433
Thank you, Son.

172
00:12:25,633 --> 00:12:26,767
Manuel?

173
00:12:29,533 --> 00:12:30,533
Manuel, you're here.

174
00:12:32,700 --> 00:12:33,767
I'll take your things.

175
00:12:33,900 --> 00:12:34,733
Come on.

176
00:12:38,100 --> 00:12:39,233
Manuel, this way.

177
00:12:46,067 --> 00:12:48,433
Good thing you're finally here.

178
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:50,700
I've been waiting for you,
Manuel.

179
00:12:53,733 --> 00:12:55,033
Welcome to our new home.

180
00:12:55,167 --> 00:12:56,400
Come.

181
00:13:03,833 --> 00:13:07,133
Manuel, I assume
you already had dinner.

182
00:13:07,267 --> 00:13:11,133
So I ordered
all the midnight snacks.

183
00:13:11,267 --> 00:13:13,500
What do you want? Pizza? Burger?

184
00:13:13,633 --> 00:13:15,833
There's chicken, fries,
and doughnuts.

185
00:13:15,967 --> 00:13:16,700
Or do you want everything?

186
00:13:16,833 --> 00:13:18,633
I just want to sleep, Hazel.

187
00:13:20,700 --> 00:13:21,667
It's still early.

188
00:13:21,833 --> 00:13:25,000
And it'd be a waste
if the food goes untouched.

189
00:13:25,133 --> 00:13:26,133
Let's talk for a bit.

190
00:13:26,267 --> 00:13:28,800
- Come on, just a little.
- No, Hazel. I'm sleepy.

191
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:38,400
<i> Son, now that Noah's back,</i>

192
00:13:38,533 --> 00:13:41,700
<i>maybe you can continue whatever
bond you had with him.</i>

193
00:13:41,833 --> 00:13:44,233
<i> Still treat him like a father.</i>

194
00:13:45,867 --> 00:13:50,300
<i>Andeng, sweetie,
do whatever you can learn now.</i>

195
00:13:50,433 --> 00:13:52,733
<i> Don't rely on me anymore.</i>

196
00:13:52,867 --> 00:13:54,867
<i>So that if we separate someday,</i>

197
00:13:55,033 --> 00:13:56,700
<i>you'll be able to stand
on your own.</i>

198
00:14:07,233 --> 00:14:08,900
Why'd you go looking for
someone to drink with?

199
00:14:12,767 --> 00:14:14,033
Something wrong?

200
00:14:18,067 --> 00:14:19,400
Man, it's big.

201
00:14:21,467 --> 00:14:23,567
I can't keep it to myself.

202
00:14:23,700 --> 00:14:25,800
I need to let it out.

203
00:14:25,933 --> 00:14:27,667
I need someone to talk to.

204
00:14:29,233 --> 00:14:31,167
I'm here, bro. I'll listen.

205
00:14:34,833 --> 00:14:36,500
Can you keep a secret?

206
00:14:37,667 --> 00:14:38,767
Of course.

207
00:14:39,100 --> 00:14:40,133
What is it?

208
00:14:46,233 --> 00:14:48,300
Dad's not home anymore.

209
00:14:50,667 --> 00:14:52,233
He went back to Hazel.

210
00:14:53,367 --> 00:14:54,733
What?

211
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,067
Lord...

212
00:15:11,233 --> 00:15:13,767
I hope...

213
00:15:13,900 --> 00:15:15,867
Manuel and I made
the right decision.

214
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:20,100
Please watch over him.

215
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:24,733
I know he'll struggle
with Hazel,

216
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:28,433
but I beg you.

217
00:15:30,533 --> 00:15:32,200
Give him strength.

218
00:15:33,533 --> 00:15:35,367
I hope...

219
00:15:35,533 --> 00:15:38,233
Please don't let him be...

220
00:15:38,367 --> 00:15:40,800
imprisoned in sorrow...

221
00:15:40,933 --> 00:15:42,533
and pain.

222
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:41,933
Joel took such nice photos.

223
00:17:42,067 --> 00:17:43,933
- In all fairness.
- We looked so happy, right?

224
00:17:44,067 --> 00:17:45,400
Especially at the bonfire.

225
00:17:47,700 --> 00:17:51,533
It would've been even better
if Didang shared the mic.

226
00:17:51,700 --> 00:17:54,467
But she had a whole
solo concert.

227
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:57,000
Why? Is there a problem
with that, Andrea?

228
00:17:57,133 --> 00:17:58,867
My voice is good.

229
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:00,800
I'm always third place
back home.

230
00:18:00,933 --> 00:18:03,433
In our town, in the province.

231
00:18:03,567 --> 00:18:04,733
Really?

232
00:18:04,867 --> 00:18:06,000
Yes.

233
00:18:06,133 --> 00:18:10,200
And such a winner because it was
for three consecutive years.

234
00:18:10,333 --> 00:18:12,000
Wow, impressive.

235
00:18:12,133 --> 00:18:13,900
How many contestants
were there?

236
00:18:14,033 --> 00:18:18,100
You're asking too many
questions. Come on, let's eat.

237
00:18:18,233 --> 00:18:19,733
Didang.

238
00:18:19,867 --> 00:18:21,600
Answer it.

239
00:18:21,767 --> 00:18:24,100
How many contestants?

240
00:18:24,233 --> 00:18:26,033
Three. Happy now?

241
00:18:26,167 --> 00:18:27,600
Alright, eat.

242
00:18:27,733 --> 00:18:28,533
Hurry up.

243
00:18:28,667 --> 00:18:30,367
Oh, wait, where's Mom?

244
00:18:30,500 --> 00:18:31,733
Why isn't she
coming down yet?

245
00:18:31,867 --> 00:18:33,100
I called her already.

246
00:18:33,233 --> 00:18:35,967
But she said she
won't join us.

247
00:18:36,100 --> 00:18:37,267
She's not feeling well.

248
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:38,900
Nauseous and dizzy.

249
00:18:39,033 --> 00:18:40,333
What?

250
00:18:40,467 --> 00:18:42,133
Why? Did she eat something bad?

251
00:18:54,300 --> 00:18:56,100
Jeff, you reek of alcohol!

252
00:18:57,167 --> 00:18:58,967
Did you drink with Dad
last night?

253
00:19:00,267 --> 00:19:02,400
Is that why he's still asleep?

254
00:19:02,533 --> 00:19:04,533
Hungover?

255
00:19:04,667 --> 00:19:06,600
Didang, can you please check?

256
00:19:06,733 --> 00:19:08,000
No, Didang, I'll do it.

257
00:19:08,133 --> 00:19:09,200
Dad's gone.

258
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:10,700
Huh?

259
00:19:12,933 --> 00:19:14,200
He left?

260
00:19:14,333 --> 00:19:15,733
Where did he go? Is he alone?

261
00:19:19,667 --> 00:19:20,933
Let's just eat.

262
00:19:21,067 --> 00:19:21,933
Jeff...

263
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:24,367
where's Dad?

264
00:19:27,067 --> 00:19:28,733
He's with Hazel.

265
00:19:28,900 --> 00:19:30,567
What?

266
00:19:30,700 --> 00:19:31,733
Why?

267
00:19:35,567 --> 00:19:37,733
He went back
to that woman.

268
00:19:37,867 --> 00:19:38,833
What?

269
00:19:58,633 --> 00:19:59,633
Mom?

270
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:02,333
Mom?

271
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:03,900
Mom?

272
00:20:05,267 --> 00:20:07,367
Mom, is it true?

273
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:09,300
Dad went back to Hazel?

274
00:20:12,167 --> 00:20:13,667
And you knew?

275
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:15,600
And you agreed?

276
00:20:20,467 --> 00:20:21,733
My head hurts.

277
00:20:21,867 --> 00:20:24,100
Don't talk to me right now.

278
00:20:24,233 --> 00:20:25,233
No, Mom.

279
00:20:25,367 --> 00:20:30,067
You need to tell us why
Dad is with Hazel right now.

280
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:31,967
And why you let him go.

281
00:20:32,933 --> 00:20:34,433
Jeffrey.

282
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:37,667
Jeffrey, take your
siblings out first.

283
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:40,933
No, Mom. We're not leaving
until you tell us the truth.

284
00:20:41,067 --> 00:20:42,767
Jeffrey, come on!

285
00:20:42,900 --> 00:20:45,000
Take your siblings out!

286
00:20:45,133 --> 00:20:47,067
My head hurts!

287
00:20:47,200 --> 00:20:48,100
- Andrea, Coleen.
- No.

288
00:20:48,233 --> 00:20:50,067
- Mom, no. No.
- Listen to Mom.

289
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:52,500
- Mom, tell us.
- What's the reason?

290
00:20:52,633 --> 00:20:53,867
- Mom!
- Come on.

291
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:56,767
- Mom!
- Mom, answer us!

292
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:57,867
- Mom!
- Mom!

293
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:59,367
- Andrea, please!
- Mom!

294
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:00,967
- Just wait, okay?
- Mom!

295
00:21:01,100 --> 00:21:02,633
Let's go!

296
00:21:02,767 --> 00:21:03,900
Mom!

297
00:21:04,033 --> 00:21:05,233
Mom!

298
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:17,467
- What are you doing? Coleen!
- Let go of me!

299
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:20,000
- Didang, stop!
- Don't be stubborn!

300
00:21:21,800 --> 00:21:23,533
Coleen! Didang!

301
00:21:24,633 --> 00:21:26,533
The kid...

302
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:29,067
You're crazy, Didang.
You don't even have a boyfriend.

303
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:31,067
Oh, right. I forgot.

304
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:32,533
Yeah.

305
00:21:40,433 --> 00:21:42,767
<i>I'm sorry, the subscriber
cannot be reached.</i>

306
00:21:42,933 --> 00:21:45,167
<i> Please try again later.</i>

307
00:21:45,300 --> 00:21:47,000
Sis, I can't contact Dad.

308
00:21:53,867 --> 00:21:56,233
Jeff, just tell us already.
What do you know?

309
00:21:57,800 --> 00:21:59,900
Or we'll go back
upstairs to Mom.

310
00:22:03,667 --> 00:22:05,767
Hey! Wait! Fine, fine, fine!

311
00:22:06,900 --> 00:22:08,267
Okay, I'll tell you.

312
00:22:13,867 --> 00:22:15,733
You already talked to Diana,
right?

313
00:22:15,900 --> 00:22:17,733
About withdrawing
your statement.

314
00:22:17,867 --> 00:22:19,133
Yes, Ma'am.

315
00:22:19,267 --> 00:22:20,567
But Ma'am,

316
00:22:20,700 --> 00:22:22,367
I'm scared.

317
00:22:22,500 --> 00:22:25,233
Because I already lied,
and now I'm taking it back?

318
00:22:25,367 --> 00:22:26,267
Why?

319
00:22:27,300 --> 00:22:28,733
You're backing out?

320
00:22:29,833 --> 00:22:31,200
Is what Jeffrey said true?

321
00:22:32,200 --> 00:22:34,633
Manuel went back to Hazel again?

322
00:22:36,233 --> 00:22:37,567
He left you all again?

323
00:22:39,567 --> 00:22:41,767
You lied to me, Dad.

324
00:22:44,567 --> 00:22:47,233
You said you believed me.

325
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:51,233
But that wasn't true.

326
00:22:51,367 --> 00:22:53,633
Tell me the truth, Manuel.

327
00:22:53,767 --> 00:22:55,267
Did Hazel threaten you?

328
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:57,633
Hazel has nothing to do
with my decision.

329
00:22:57,767 --> 00:22:59,433
I went back to her on my own.

330
00:22:59,567 --> 00:23:02,133
So that's why
she was at the resort.

331
00:23:02,267 --> 00:23:03,633
Because you had an agreement!

332
00:23:05,833 --> 00:23:07,233
You went to the resort?
